      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but i've been reading some stuff online saying that originalism is basically just a way for judges to push a conservative agenda under the guise of law. how do scholars who disagree with originalism respond to that? like, is there a legitimate critique of the theory or is it mostly just a political disagreement?",
